<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-19T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/256: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-20T12:00:00+08:00">January 20,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 20—9
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. Legation’s 1201, Dec. 30, 9 a.m.,<note n="53" xml:id="d446fn53">Not
                                printed.</note> and 6, January 2, 5 p.m. Norwegian Chargé d’Affaires
                            left yesterday for Nanking to engage in extraterritoriality
                            negotiations. Norwegian Minister for Foreign Affairs informed British
                            Minister in Oslo that the Norwegian Government was prepared to follow
                            the lead of the British Government in matters relating to the
                            relinquishment of extraterritorial rights.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>